Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @garlic clove{2}(minced). Slice the @courgette{1} lengthways into ½cm strips. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1/2} in half.

Next cut three-quarters of your @mozzarella{1}(sliced) into slices, as thin as you can (keep a quarter for your salad). Press #kitchen paper{} or a clean #tea towel{} onto each slice to soak up as much excess moisture as possible.

Add a splash of @olive oil{a splash} to a #pan{} and fry your red onion and garlic on medium-low heat for around ~{5%mins}, or until soft.

> You can start the next step at the same time to save some time.

Add in the @tomato passata{1} with a @salt{pinch}, the @dried oregano{3/4} and a few grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}. Bubble the mixture for ~{5%mins}, then remove from the heat to cool down.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, fry your courgette strips in batches. Cook them for ~{1%minute} on each side and then keep to the side. Do not overcrowd the pan as this will stew the courgette rather than brown it.

Put enough (about a third) of your passata in an #ovenproof dish{} to thinly cover the bottom. Top this with a layer of your courgette (you should use roughly half your courgette here as you're going to repeat this step!). Next, layer on a couple of slices of mozzarella, followed by some torn @basil{1}(torn) and half of the @pine nuts{25}.

Spread on another layer of passata, followed by your remaining courgette, a couple more slices of mozzarella and bit more basil (save some of each for your salad) and the rest of your pine nuts. Finally add one more layer of passata and top your parmigiana with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{3} and the @panko breadcrumbs{20}. Bake in your oven for ~{15%mins}.

== Insalata Caprese ==

Tear up a small handful of basil leaves and the remaining mozzarella. Toss these and your cherry tomatoes in a #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle} and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Serve your parmigiana with your salad and @foccacia{1} on the side.